# Comment discipline

When writing or editing code, keep comments lean:

- Explain *why*, not *what*. Don't narrate code (`// increment counter`) or restate signatures.
- No notes-to-self / changelog comments (`// as requested`, `// updated to handle X`, `// this should now...`). That belongs in the PR, not the code.
- No commented-out code. No giant header blocks where one inline note would do.
- Keep doc comments on public/exported APIs where the project requires them — trim everywhere else.
- A comment earns its place only if it adds what the code can't: intent, trade-offs, constraints, gotchas, links to context.
